Fig. 4 shows a battery in the constant current discharge (duration t




         discharge


), standing (duration toff), constant current charging (duration t




         charge


) under the action of three stages, its terminal voltage amplitude change curve. This is a kind of hybrid power pulse test (Hybrid Power Pulse Test, HPPT) commonly used internationally. By testing this curve, the ohmic internal resistance corresponding to the battery can be obtained, and the value of the polarization capacitance of each polarization resistance can also be fitted.
